</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="199" pageNumber="478" type="breeding">
<paragraph blockId="199.[107,1315,2620,3127]" pageId="199" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[108,242,2856,2889]" pageId="199" pageNumber="478">Breeding.</emphasis>
Five pregnant Day’s Grass Mice had 2-5 embryos (mean three), with pregnancies recorded in March and June-July. Juveniles were collected in March.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
